          "tz": 240
        },
        "subject": "LU-413 osc: do not miss preallocated objects",
        "message": "LU-413 osc: do not miss preallocated objects\n\nosc_precreate, osc_create, handle_async_create used to check\nOSCC_FLAG_NOSPC before checking for preallocated objects, that\ndid not allow to use all OST objects. Move checks for\nOSCC_FLAG_NOSPC past checking for preallocated objects.\n\nChange filter_precreate to return 0 if it manages to precreate\nat least one object.\n\nWith these changes there is no need to limit number of files\ncreated by performance tests.\n\nSigned-off-by: Vladimir Saveliev <vladimir.saveliev@oracle.com>\nChange-Id: I03f734ff684416edc8cebf821b79c733754f6aa6\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b1_8"
    }
  },
